parameters.text:
=Analyze this email and classify it according to the system prompt criteria.

📧 EMAIL INFORMATION:
- From: {{ $('Fetch Email Details').item.json.from }}
- To: {{ $('Fetch Email Details').item.json.to }}
- CC: {{ $('Fetch Email Details').item.json.cc }}
- Subject: {{ $('Fetch Email Details').item.json.subject }}
- Body: {{ $('Fetch Email Details').item.json.text }}
- Headers: {{ JSON.stringify($('Fetch Email Details').item.json.headers) }}
- Date: {{ $('Get Current Date').item.json.date }}

⚠️ IMPORTANT REMINDERS:
- If the email is part of a thread, use the THREAD tool to retrieve the full context
- Check whether the user is a DIRECT recipient (To) or only in CC
- Check if the email is addressed directly to the user (e.g. "Hello", "Hi" with intent)
- Apply the "Reply" or "Urgent" tag ONLY if the email is addressed directly to the user
- Apply the "Invoice" tag to emails mentioning invoices
- Adapt tone (formal/informal) based on the email received
- If a meeting is requested, use the CALENDAR tool to propose real time slots
- For emails with specific requests, respond as if the task has already been completed

Return your response in the exact JSON format specified in the system prompt.

parameters.jsCode:
var date = new Date().toISOString();
var day = new Date().getDay();
const weekday = ["Dimanche", "Lundi", "Mardi", "Mercredi", "Jeudi", "Vendredi", "Samedi"];

items[0].json.date_today = date;
items[0].json.day_today = weekday[day];

return items;

